					<h1>Adjusting the Text Size</h1>
					<br />
					<p>The FedsHireVets website allows you to change the text size through standard browser settings or keyboard shortcuts:</p>
					<h3>Standard Browser Settings</h3>
					<h4>Internet Explorer</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>In the <strong>View</strong> menu, mouse over to Text Size</li>
						<li>Select the Text Size that best works for you: Largest to Smallest</li>
					</ol>
					<h4>Firefox</h4>
					<p>From the <strong>View</strong> menu, select <strong>Zoom</strong>, then <strong>Zoom In</strong> or <strong>Zoom Out</strong> to increase or decrease the font size.<br />
					<strong>Note:</strong> For Firefox 4+, your full menu bar will need to be enabled; you cannot complete the previous instructions with the minimized/hidden menu bar.</p>
					<h4>Chrome</h4>
					<p>Temporarily change the font size for the current window:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>From the <strong>Tools</strong> menu (the wrench in the upper right-hand corner), click <strong>Zoom +</strong> or <strong>Zoom -</strong>.</li>
					</ol>
					<p>Permanently change the font size for all Chrome windows:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>From the <strong>Tools</strong> menu (the wrench in the upper right-hand corner), select <strong>Options</strong>.</li>
						<li>From the <strong>Under the Hood</strong> tab, scroll down to <strong>Web Content</strong>, and select the appropriate <strong>Font Size</strong>.</li>
						<li>Close the <strong>Under the Hood</strong> tab and return to your content.</li>
					</ol>
					<br /><br />
					<h3>Use Keyboard Shortcuts</h3>
					<p>In Windows, use the following keyboard shortcuts:</p>
					<blockquote>
						<p>Increase: Ctrl-plus sign ( + ) or Ctrl-equals sign ( = )<br />
						Decrease: Ctrl-minus sign ( - )<br />
						Return to default font size: Ctrl-0 (zero)</p>
					</blockquote>
					<p>In Mac OS X, use the Command key instead of Ctrl.</p>
